messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
We need an ambulance at 1397 Newport.
1397 Newport?
Correct.
What is the problem there?
I think we have a dead person in here.
Okay. Is the person bleeding at all?
Yes, yes.
How old is this person?
23, male or female?
Female. I have a mother. She's right now seeing the daughter laying on the ground. She found her laying on the ground.
Okay, you're not going to hear me for a second, but do not hang up.
Okay.
Okay, ma'am. Tell me exactly what happened.
I don't know what happened. I got home. We found her laying down in the garage. Somebody stabbed her with a knife.
Somebody stabbed her with a knife?
Yes. We need the ambulance as fast as we can. She still has a heartbeat, but she's cold.
She still has a heartbeat, but she's cold?
She's cold and blue.
She's cold and blue. Do you know how long she's been there?
I don't know. I just got home from work.
Okay. We do have police officers en route and an ambulance also, okay? I want you to stay on the phone with me until they get there. She's still in the garage right now?
Yes. I'm scared to move her.
Don't move her, okay? You said that she still has a heartbeat, though?
Yes, I think so.
Do you know who did this?
I don't know. I don't know.
Do you see a knife?
No, I don't see the knife.
Okay. Who else is at the house with you, ma'am?
Her mom right now.
Is there anyone else at the house?
No, no one.
Okay, so you just got home now?
Yes. We found her in the garage. We were walking and we were trying to reach her. We couldn't find her. She was not answering the phone.
Okay, how long were you guys trying to reach her?
Since 9 p.m.
Okay, yes ma'am, they're on the way, okay? They're getting there as fast as they can. Just take a deep breath. What's her name?
Her name is Alina.
Can you spell it?
A-L-I-N-A.
And what's her last name?
Ribnikova. R-I-B-N-I-K-O-V-A.
And she's 23?
She's 22, I think.
Okay. What's your name?
Victoria.
Okay. What's your relation to her?
We are roommates and she's my best friend.
Okay. Where are you right now?
I'm trying to pull out the cars from the driveway.
You're moving the cars out of the driveway?
Yes.
How many cars you have in the driveway?
We have two cars in the driveway.
Just leave the cars where they are, okay? The ambulance can get around them.
Okay, okay.
Are you in a vehicle in the driveway?
No, I'm right now in the garage. I put my car but there's still two more cars.
There are still two more cars?
Yes.
Do you see the police officers now?
There is one police officer here.
Okay. We've got more police officers and the ambulance will be there shortly, okay?
Okay.
I'll let you talk to the police officers now, okay? You can hang up with me.
Okay, goodbye.
